{"key":"processedPost-9128594","value":{"id":9128594,"first":9127508,"last":9128594,"when":1224896940,"utime":"10/25/08 04:09 AM","content":"Cakes are great to learn on, and many experienced growers still use them to test isolated strains.&nbsp; <br /><br />There is no faster way to go from spores to fruits than with brf tek, and there's no substrate yet developed that will deliver the biological efficiency of brf cakes.&nbsp; <br /><br />You can mix up a batch of twelve brf cakes for less than ten dollars, and get a nice yield with about an eighth ounce per cake on first flush.&nbsp; That's not shabby at all for about 90 cents worth of brown rice and verm per cake.&nbsp; If you want more, grow bulk, but trashing teks that perform well is just plain juvenile.<br />RR","title":"Re: Trusted spore distributors?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}